name: Mid90s
title: 2018 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 1h 25m
description: In 1990s Los Angeles, a 13-year-old spends his summer navigating between a troubled home life and a crew of new friends he meets at a skate shop.

name: Frances Ha
title: 2012 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 26m
description: When Frances's friend and room-mate Sophie moves out, Frances is left to fend for herself. Frances experiences new adventures in the city, where she also finds love and makes a decent living.

name: Aftersun
title: 2022 ‧ Drama/Coming-of-age story ‧ 1h 42m
description: Twenty years after their last holiday at a fading vacation resort, Sophie reflects on the rare time spent with her loving and idealistic father Calum. At 11-years-old, as the world of adolescence creeps into Sophie's view, Calum struggles under the weight of life outside of fatherhood. Sophie's recollections become a powerful and heartrending portrait of their relationship, as she tries to reconcile the father she knew with the man she didn't.

name: Call Me by Your Name
title: 2017 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 2h 10m
description: Elio, a teenager, develops feelings for Oliver, his father's temporary assistant. Although their relationship is temporary, Elio realises his sexual orientation and tries to come to terms with it.

name: Eddie the Eagle
title: 2016 ‧ Sport/Comedy ‧ 1h 46m
description: Eddie Edwards, an underdog ski-jumper, tackles various challenges in order to become the first participant to represent Great Britain in Olympic ski-jumping.

name: Lucas
title: 1986 ‧ Romance/Sport ‧ 1h 40m
description: Lucas (Corey Haim) is an unusually bright teenager whose nerdy looks and meek demeanor make him a favorite target for bullies. His life at school seems to improve when he befriends Maggie (Kerri Green), a cute new girl whose love interest, Cappie (Charlie Sheen), protects him from harassment. However, despite his friend Rina's (Winona Ryder) clear affection for him, Lucas falls for Maggie, and in a final effort to impress her, joins the high school football team.

name: Garden State
title: 2004 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 42m
description: Andrew, a young troubled man, returns home after a decade to attend the funeral of his mother. However, what follows ahead is a journey of self-realization that changes him forever.

name: Hotel Chevalier
title: 2007 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 13 mins
description: A man (Jason Schwartzman) and a woman (Natalie Portman) converse in a hotel room.

name: The Darwin Awards
title: 2006 ‧ Comedy/Adventure ‧ 1h 34m
description: A forensic officer and an insurance investigator investigate a potential award, honoring those who improve the species by accidentally removing themselves from it!"

title: 1988 ‧ War/Drama ‧ 1h 35m
description: Friends Ralph and Scott decide to leave town to avoid being drafted during the Vietnam War. Their lives are changed forever after they learn that Scott's brother Alden is missing.

name: Star Wars: Episode II - Attack of the Clones
title: 2002 ‧ Family/Action ‧ 2h 22m
description: While pursuing an assassin, Obi Wan uncovers a sinister plot to destroy the Republic. With the fate of the galaxy hanging in the balance, the Jedi must defend the galaxy against the evil Sith.

name: Hesher
title: 2010 ‧ Comedy/Thriller ‧ 1h 49m
description: After the death of his mother in a car accident, T J, a young boy, loses touch with the rest of his family and falls into depression. Things worsen when he meets Hesher, a foul-mouthed squatter.

name: Christiane F.
title: 1981 ‧ Drama/Indie film ‧ 2h 18m
description: 13-year-old Christiane Felscherinow resides in Berlin with her mother. She starts abusing dangerous substances after she falls in love with Detlev, which causes her to steal from her house, sell all of her assets, and descend to abysmal levels.

name: Speak
title: 2004 ‧ Drama/Indie film ‧ 1h 32m
description: Freshman high-school student Melinda (Kristen Stewart) has refused to speak ever since she called the cops on a popular summer party. With her old friends snubbing her for being a rat, and her parents (Elizabeth Perkins, D.B. Sweeney) too busy to notice her troubles, she folds into herself, trying to hide her secret: that star senior Andy (Eric Lively) raped her at the party. But Melinda does manage to find solace in her art class headed by Mr. Freeman (Steve Zahn).

name: Lilya 4-ever
title: 2002 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 1h 49m
description: Lilya (Oksana Akinshina) lives in poverty and dreams of a better life. Her mother moves to the United States and abandons her to her aunt (Liliya Shinkaryova), who neglects her. Lilya hangs out with her friends, Natasha (Elina Benenson) and Volodya (Artiom Bogucharski), who is suicidal. Desperate for money, she starts working as a prostitute, and later meets Andrei (Pavel Ponomaryov). He offers her a good job in Sweden, but when Lilya arrives her life quickly enters a downward spiral.

name: Buffalo '66
title: 1998 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 50m
description: Billy kidnaps a young dancer, Layla, and asks her to pretend to be his wife so that he can please his parents. While Layla is initially hesitant, she falls in love with him.

name: But I'm a Cheerleader
title: 1999 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 25m
description: Megan (Natasha Lyonne) considers herself a typical American girl. She excels in school and cheerleading, and she has a handsome football-playing boyfriend, even though she isn't that crazy about him. So she's stunned when her parents decide she's gay and send her to True Directions, a boot camp meant to alter her sexual orientation. While there, Megan meets a rebellious and unashamed teen lesbian, Graham (Clea DuVall). Though Megan still feels confused, she starts to have feelings for Graham.

name: The Perks of Being a Wallflower
title: 2012 ‧ Romance/Comedy ‧ 1h 45m
description: Charlie, a 15-year-old introvert, enters high school and is nervous about his new life. When he befriends his seniors, he learns to cope with his friend's suicide and his tumultuous past.

name: Black Swan
title: 2010 ‧ Horror/Drama ‧ 1h 48m
description: Nina, a ballerina, gets the chance to play the White Swan, Princess Odette. But she finds herself slipping into madness when Thomas, the artistic director, decides that Lily might fit the role better.

name: To the Bone
title: 2017 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 1h 47m
description: Ellen is an unruly 20-year-old anorexic girl who spent the better part of her teenage years being shepherded through various recovery programmes, only to find herself several pounds lighter every time.

name: Margin Call
title: 2011 ‧ Thriller/Drama ‧ 1h 47m
description: A financial company's management division head working on a major analysis is fired. His protege attempts to complete the analysis and finds out the true reason behind their financial downfall.

name: 'Gator Bait
title: 1973 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 1h 31m
description: A Cajun beauty (Claudia Jennings) lures male intruders into a swamp where women have a field day with them.

name: The Girls from Thunder Strip
title: 1970 ‧ Action/Drama ‧ 1h 20m
description: A group of female bootleggers take on a murderous biker gang, led by Teach. The situation becomes even more complicated when a federal agent shows up to shut down their illicit operation.

name: Black Gunn
title: 1972 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 37m
description: Life is good for Gunn (Jim Brown). Not only does he live in a huge Los Angeles mansion with his beautiful girlfriend (Brenda Sykes), he's also converted it into one of the most most happening clubs in the city. But life isn't as good for his little brother, Scotty, a troubled Vietnam vet involved with a group of black militants. When Scotty and the radicals rob a gambling parlor owned by the mob, the gangsters strike back, and Scotty ends up dead. Now Gunn is out for revenge.

name: Hammer
title: 1972 ‧ Action/Drama ‧ 1h 32m
description: B J Hammer is hired by a shady manager and begins a lucrative career as a boxer. However, things take a turn when the mafia wants him to throw an important match and kidnap his girlfriend.

name: Trouble Man
title: 1972 ‧ Action/Crime ‧ 1h 39m
description: T (Robert Hooks) is a slick detective who's done very well for himself, but still runs his operation from the same mean streets he grew up on in South Central Los Angeles. His latest case comes from local hoods Chalky (Paul Winfield) and Pete (Ralph Waite), who claim that someone's been robbing their dice games at gunpoint. As T searches for the perpetrator, he realizes the job is a setup. Chalky and Pete have pinned a murder on him, and both cops and criminals think T is to blame.

name: One Down, Two to Go
title: 1982 ‧ Action/Drama ‧ 1h 24m
description: Buddies Cal (Fred Williamson), J. (Jim Brown), Chuck (Jim Kelly) and Ralph even the score for a rip-off martial-arts tournament.

name: Disco Godfather
title: 1979 ‧ Action/Comedy ‧ 1h 33m
description: A retired police officer, who becomes a celebrity at the Blueberry Hill disco, continues his fight against the drug peddlers. Thereafter, he eventually tracks down the drug kingpin.

name: Youngblood
title: 1978 ‧ Action/Drama ‧ 1h 44m
description: A realistic gang war/drug story set in the ghetto, about the coming of age of a fifteen year old black kid, his involvement with a street gang, and their war against dope pushers.

name: Penitentiary
title: 1979 ‧ Sport/Action ‧ 1h 39m
description: After getting into a fight that leaves a man dead, Martel Gordone is sentenced to prison. He joins the prison boxing team hoping to get an early parole.

name: Killer of Sheep
title: 1978 ‧ Drama/Narrative ‧ 1h 15m
description: The story revolves around Stan, who must struggle against influences that would dishonour and endanger him and his family.

name: Scarface
title: 1983 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 45m
description: Tony Montana and his close friend Manny, build a strong drug empire in Miami. However as his power begins to grow, so does his ego and his enemies, and his own paranoia begins to plague his empire.

name: Black Samson
title: 1974 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 38m
description: A nightclub owner (Rockne Tarkington) with a pet lion rids his neighborhood of a white mobster (William Smith).

name: Black Belt Jones
title: 1974 ‧ Action/Adventure ‧ 1h 27m
description: A martial artist battles the Mafia and ghetto hoods to keep a karate school from falling into the wrong hands. Will the Mafia win or will Black Belt Jones save the day?

name: Switchblade Sisters
title: 1975 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 31m
description: The leader (Robbie Lee) of an all-girl gang feels threatened by a tough new member (Joanne Nail).

name: The Big Doll House
title: 1971 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 35m
description: Women (Judy Brown, Pam Grier, Roberta Collins) in pastel dresses plot an escape from a tropical island prison run by perverts.

name: Slaughter's Big Rip-Off
title: 1973 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 34m
description: In this sequel to "Slaughter," former Green Beret Slaughter (Jim Brown) moves to Los Angeles hoping to start a new life after having taken out a mob syndicate in South America. He isn't there long, however, before a hit man in a biplane tries to kill him at a swanky party. Realizing the syndicate is still alive under the leadership of criminal kingpin Duncan (Ed McMahon), Slaughter wants to skip town, but a well-meaning cop (Brock Peters) blackmails him into staying and fighting.

name: Melinda
title: 1972 ‧ Action/Drama ‧ 1h 49m
description: Frankie, a radio disc jockey who also takes karate lessons, falls for a mysterious woman who claims her name is Melinda. However, his life changes when he finds her dead in his apartment.

name: The Candy Tangerine Man
title: 1975 ‧ Action/Adventure ‧ 1h 35m
description: The Candy Tangerine Man is a 1975 American action-adventure blaxploitation film starring John Daniels, Eli Haines and Tom Hankason. Distributed by Moonstone Entertainment, it follows the story of the powerful "Black Baron", both a pimp and a doting father.

name: Black Mama White Mama
title: 1973 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 27m
description: Lee Daniels (Pam Grier) is a black girl busted for prostitution. Karen Brent (Margaret Markov) is a white girl arrested for her involvement with a local revolutionary group. The two women meet in jail and, despite their mutual animosity, are chained together for transport to a maximum security prison. Their bus is ambushed en route, however, and the pair manages to escape together. Chased by bounty hunters, crooked police and revolutionaries, they struggle to get along and get away.

name: Hell Up in Harlem
title: 1973 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 34m
description: Hell Up in Harlem is a 1973 blaxploitation American neo-noir film, starring Fred Williamson and Gloria Hendry. Written and directed by Larry Cohen, it is a sequel to the film Black Caesar. The film's soundtrack was recorded by Edwin Starr and released by Motown Records in January 1974.

name: Friday Foster
title: 1975 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 30m
description: On assignment from her editor, photographer Friday Foster (Pam Grier) travels to an airport to capture a few shots of the richest black man in the United States (Thalmus Rasulala). But it turns out Foster isn't the only one taking shots as she witnesses -- and photographs -- an assassination attempt on her subject. With definitive evidence in her possession, she also becomes a target of the assassins. Joining a private eye (Yaphet Kotto), Foster sets out to discover the truth behind the attempt.

name: Sheba, Baby
title: 1975 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 31m
description: Sheba Shayne, a hard-bitten private investigator from Chicago, returns to her hometown in Louisville to protect her father from a group of thugs who want to take over his business.

name: Newman's Law
title: 1974 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 38m
description: Vince Newman (George Peppard), a hard-nosed Los Angeles cop, is loyal to his partner Garry (Roger Robinson), devoted to his family and far too principled to take a bribe. So when he gets booted from duty after being falsely accused of extortion, he decides to go rogue and keep investigating an organized crime case he was working on. As he digs deeper, he stumbles upon a conspiracy that might extend beyond the local mob scene, perhaps even to the highest reaches of his own department.

name: The Shining
title: 1980 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 2h 26m
description: Jack Torrance is a winter caretaker at the Overlook Hotel. He lives there with his wife Wendy and son Danny. However, things take a turn when Danny and his family start witnessing supernatural events.

name: Rolling Thunder
title: 1977 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 35m
description: Tragedy strikes in Major Charles' life, when his wife and child are killed by a gang of thugs. Determined to seek revenge, he sets out with his friend Johnny to eliminate the murderers.

name: Shaft's Big Score!
title: 1972 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 45m
description: When John Shaft investigates the murder of his friend who ran a money laundering racket with an unaccounted $200,000, he gets embroiled in a battle between two rival gangs that aimed to get the money.

name: Trick Baby
title: 1972 ‧ Action/Drama ‧ 1h 34m
description: The son of a black prostitute and a white client, Johnny "Folks" O'Brien (Kiel Martin) spends his childhood in the ghetto hearing the hateful name "trick baby," only to realize as an adult just how useful it is to pass for white. Together with his mentor, con man "Blue" Howard (Mel Stewart), Folks succeeds in ripping off many of Philadelphia's wealthy whites with a clever diamond scam. The streak ends, however, when his latest victim turns out to be the father of a local Mafioso.

name: Hit Man
title: 1972 ‧ Action/Crime ‧ 1h 30m
description: When small-time hoodlum Tyrone Tackett hears that his brother's death was murder, he finds himself witnessing a whole new side of crime, when his investigations lead him into LA's underground pornography world.

name: Bucktown
title: 1975 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 34m
description: Duke enlists his friend Roy and his gang's help to fight against a few corrupt cops who killed his brother, a nightclub owner. However, Roy's men end up trying to take control, leaving Duke worried.

name: Three the Hard Way
title: 1974 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 45m
description: A record producer (Jim Brown), a PR man (Fred Williamson) and a black belt (Jim Kelly) in karate foil a racist plot to poison part of a city.

name: Dolemite
title: 1975 ‧ Comedy/Action ‧ 1h 30m
description: Dolemite, a pimp, is framed for a crime and is jailed for 20 years. However, his associates plan an escape for him and vow revenge on Green, the rival gang member responsible for framing him.

name: The Education of Sonny Carson
title: 1974 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 44m
description: Caught up in gang life, a gifted young man (Rony Clanton) goes to jail and finally pulls himself out of it.

name: Super Fly
title: 1972 ‧ Crime/Action ‧ 1h 33m
description: Priest, a cocaine dealer, decides to put an end to his wrongdoings before one final crime. However, he does not find it easy and encounters troubles.

name: Lady Sings the Blues
title: 1972 ‧ Drama/Melodrama ‧ 2h 24m
description: A behind-the-scenes look at the movie 'Lady Sings the Blues', where actress Diana Ross discusses her role as Billie Holiday.

name: Truck Turner
title: 1974 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 31m
description: Truck, a bounty hunter, gets a job to track down Gator, a pimp. Truck and his friend chase Gator but he dies during the chase. His girlfriend Dorinda decides to avenge Gator's death.

name: Sweet Sweetback's Baadasssss Song
title: 1971 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 1h 37m
description: Sweet Sweetback (Melvin Van Peebles) is a black orphan who, having grown up in a brothel, now works there as part of a sex show. When the police need a patsy for a murder in the black community, Sweetback's employer gives him up to two white cops, whom Sweetback ends up killing. Suddenly the target of a massive manhunt, he decides to flee to Mexico. As he makes his way there, he is captured by, and escapes from, both the cops and a chapter of the Hell's Angels.

name: Across 110th Street
title: 1972 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 1h 42m
description: Two cops, Pope and Mattelli, are looking for three robbers-cum-murderers who ran away with $300,000 that belonged to the Italian mob. Will they find them before sadistic Mafia henchman D'Salvio?

name: Enter the Dragon
title: 1973 ‧ Action/Crime ‧ 1h 42m
description: Lee, a Shaolin martial artist, helps the British Intelligence in an undercover mission to nab Han, who is involved in drug trafficking and sex trade.

name: Cleopatra Jones
title: 1973 ‧ Action/Crime ‧ 1h 29m
description: Cleopatra, a special undercover agent, is tasked with overseeing the destruction of a farm of poppies owned by Mommy, an evil drug lord. Enraged, Mommy plots to exact revenge on Cleopatra.

name: Coffy
title: 1973 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 31m
description: After her sister succumbs to heroin addiction, Coffy decides to put an end to the illegal drug trade. She is left devastated when she learns that her boyfriend is involved in the illegal drug trade.

name: Uptown Saturday Night
title: 1974 ‧ Comedy/Action ‧ 1h 44m
description: Blue-collar buddies (Sidney Poitier, Bill Cosby) search the underworld for a winning lottery ticket lost in a nightclub holdup.

name: Willie Dynamite
title: 1973 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 42m
description: When enterprising pimp Willie Dynamite (Roscoe Orman) refuses to agree to a mandate that would assign pimps to specific districts, he sets himself on a collision course with Bell (Roger Robinson), the kingpin of New York prostitution. Worse yet, Willie comes under the scrutiny of a pair of detectives. And then there's Cora (Diana Sands), a former prostitute now employed as a social worker, who aims to take down Willie's operation by preaching reform to his girls.

name: Black Caesar
title: 1973 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 1h 34m
description: Tired of the racism that is rampant all around him, a kid from New York City's Harlem vows to take charge of the city's crime world.

name: Super Fly T.N.T.
title: 1973 ‧ Action/Drama ‧ 1h 27m
description: A Harlem drug dealer (Ron O'Neal) and his girlfriend (Sheila Frazier) retire to Rome, where he joins an African revolution.

name: The Mack
title: 1973 ‧ Crime/Drama ‧ 1h 50m
description: John 'Goldie' Mickens is released after five years from prison and decides to become a pimp. When he refuses to join his former gang, things take an unexpected turn that leads to his mother's death.

name: Why Did I Get Married?
title: 2007 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 1h 53m
description: Four married couples take a week's vacation each year where the only agenda is asking themselves 'why did I get married?' This time, each couple's relationship is exposed as secrets are laid bare.

name: A Haunted House
title: 2013 ‧ Horror/Comedy ‧ 1h 26m
description: Malcom and Kisha's lives are turned upside down when Kisha gets possessed by the demon inside their newly-purchased house. Malcolm seeks the help of experts to get his sex life back.

name: Scary Movie 2
title: 2001 ‧ Horror/Comedy ‧ 1h 23m
description: Professor Oldman convinces four teenagers to spend a night in a haunted house. Once there, they encounter strange happenings and decide to get rid of the ghost.

name: I Am Sam
title: 2001 ‧ Drama ‧ 2h 12m
description: Sam, a man with special needs, fights for the custody of his daughter when her mother abandons them. He tries to prove that he is a capable father with the help of an infamous lawyer.

name: Mona Lisa Smile
title: 2003 ‧ Romance/Comedy ‧ 1h 57m
description: Katherine Watson teaches art history in 1953 at the respectable all-female Wellesley College. She encourages her conservative students to question and disregard the outdated societal mores for women.

name: Material Girls
title: 2006 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 38m
description: Tanzie and Ava are two wealthy sisters and heiresses to the family's cosmetics fortune. Their life takes a u-turn after a scandal and the following investigation almost brings them to the streets.

name: Love, Simon
title: 2018 ‧ Romance/Comedy ‧ 1h 50m
description: Simon Spier keeps his sexual orientation a secret from his family. However, when a blackmailer threatens to reveal it, he goes on a roller-coaster journey to come to terms with his identity.

name: Bottoms
title: 2023 ‧ Comedy ‧ 1h 32m
description: Unpopular best friends PJ and Josie start a high school fight club to meet girls and lose their virginity. They soon find themselves in over their heads when the most popular students start beating each other up in the name of self-defense.

name: The Wedding Date
title: 2005 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 30m
description: Kat Ellis is all set to be the maid of honor at her younger sister's wedding. She is taken back when she finds out that the best man is none other than her ex-fiance.

name: Charlie's Angels: Full Throttle
title: 2003 ‧ Action/Comedy ‧ 1h 52m
description: The Angels carry out an investigation of a sequence of murders which take place after the theft of the contents of a profile database related to FBI's witness protection programme.

name: Sydney White
title: 2007 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 48m
description: After being banished from the most popular sorority on campus, Sydney White teams up with a group of socially awkward outcasts to outdo the queen at her own game.

name: My Big Fat Greek Wedding
title: 2002 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 35m
description: Toula, a Greek woman trying to come to terms with her heritage, falls in love with a non-Greek man, and has to convince her family to accept him.

name: While You Were Sleeping
title: 1995 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 43m
description: When Lucy, a token collector, saves passenger Peter's life, she is mistaken for his fiancee by his family. While Peter is in a coma, things complicate as Lucy begins to fall in love with his brother.

name: Maid in Manhattan
title: 2002 ‧ Romance/Comedy ‧ 1h 45m
description: A maid in a luxurious hotel is mistaken as a guest by a rich political candidate. They spend a romantic night together. However, they decide to part ways after her true identity is revealed.

name: Step Brothers
title: 2008 ‧ Comedy ‧ 1h 38m
description: Brennan and Dale, two middle-aged men who still live with their parents, are forced to stay under the same roof together when Brennan's mother marries Dale's father.

name: Baby's Day Out
title: 1994 ‧ Family/Comedy ‧ 1h 39m
description: Bink is the mischievous baby of a rich couple. As the couple gears up to have their baby's picture appear in the social pages of the newspaper, three criminals, posing as photographers, kidnap Bink.

name: Mama Jack
title: 2005 ‧ Comedy ‧ 1h 44m
description: Complications arise when a fugitive (Leon Schuster), who's masquerading as a woman, falls in love with his pretty boss (Mary-Anne Barlow).

name: The Pacifier
title: 2005 ‧ Family/Comedy ‧ 1h 35m
description: Shane Wolfe must rescue Howard Plummer. Plummer, who is working on a secret government assignment, is killed. Wolfe must now search for the assignment in his house where his five children live.

name: Don't Be a Menace to South Central While Drinking Your Juice in the Hood
title: 1996 ‧ Comedy/Mystery ‧ 1h 34m
description: Ashtray, a young black man, is sent to live in the ghetto with his father where he learns about the realities of life on the streets and how to become a man from his friends and relatives.

name: I Got the Hook-Up
title: 1998 ‧ Comedy/Action/Adventure ‧ 1h 43m
description: Two friends come across a box full of cell phones. However, their so-called jackpot invites a nightmare when the Federal Bureau of Investigation chases them.

name: Bad Boys
title: 1995 ‧ Action/Comedy ‧ 1h 59m
description: Marcus and Mike, best friends and detectives with the narcotics department, set out to find the criminal responsible for stealing $100 million worth heroin from the police department.

name: Bad Boys II
title: 2003 ‧ Action/Comedy ‧ 2h 27m
description: Mike and Marcus, the Miami Police Department detectives, investigate the flow of drugs into Miami. Their search leads them to a dangerous drug lord who is planning to control the city's drug trade.

name: Deuce Bigalow: Male Gigolo
title: 1999 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 1h 28m
description: A cleaner takes care of a fish that belongs to a gigolo while he is away on a business trip. But when he wrecks the gigolo's house, the cleaner is forced to become a gigolo to earn some money.

name: White Chicks
title: 2004 ‧ Comedy/Crime ‧ 1h 49m
description: Two disgraced FBI agents, Kevin Copeland and Marcus Copeland, are assigned a new case where they must protect Tiffany and Brittany Wilson, two cruise line heiresses, from getting abducted.

name: Warfare
title: 2025 ‧ War ‧ 1h 35m
description: A surveillance mission goes wrong for a platoon of American Navy SEALs in insurgent territory in Iraq.

name: Sinners
title: 2025 ‧ Horror/Adventure ‧ 2h 17m
description: Trying to leave their troubled lives behind, twin brothers return to their Mississippi hometown to start again, only to discover that an even greater evil is waiting to welcome them back.

name: Novocaine
title: 2025 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 50m
description: When the girl of his dreams gets kidnapped, a man turns his inability to feel pain into an unexpected advantage as he fights a bunch of thugs to get her back.

name: Fight or Flight
title: 2025 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 41m
description: A mercenary takes on the job of tracking a high-value asset known only as "The Ghost" on an international flight. Realizing the plane is filled with assassins assigned to kill them both, the pair must work together in a fight for their lives.

name: Havoc
title: 2025 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 45m
description: After a drug deal gone wrong, a bruised detective must fight his way through the criminal underworld to rescue a politician's estranged son, unravelling a deep web of corruption and conspiracy that ensnares his entire city.

name: The Amateur
title: 2025 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 2h 5m
description: Charlie Heller is a brilliant CIA decoder whose world comes crashing down when his wife dies in a London terrorist attack. When his supervisors refuse to take action, his intelligence becomes the ultimate weapon as he embarks on a dangerous trek across the globe to track down those responsible.

name: A Working Man
title: 2025 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 56m
description: Levon Cade left behind a decorated military career in the black ops to live a simple life of working construction. However, when human traffickers kidnap his boss's daughter, his search to bring her home uncovers a world of corruption far greater than he ever could have imagined.

name: Vongozero: The Outbreak
title: 2019 ‧ Sci-fi/Thriller ‧ 1h 30m
description: A deadly virus of unknown origin has decimated Moscow. Sergey, along with his girlfriend and their autistic son are joined by his ex-wife, their son and several fellows to escape the quarantine zone lest they suffer a slow and painful death. Vongozero: The Outbreak (Theatrical Version)Directed by Pavel Kostomarov.

name: The Deep End of the Ocean
title: 1999 ‧ Family/Thriller ‧ 1h 45m
description: Beth and her husband, Pat, are devastated when their son mysteriously disappears during Beth's school reunion. However, their lives change when a familiar-looking boy turns up at their house.

name: Radio
title: 2003 ‧ Sport/Comedy ‧ 1h 49m
description: Football coach Jones meets the 23-year-old Robert 'Radio' Kennedy and notices his limitations and shortcomings. He takes him under his wing and mentors him to become a well-mannered gentleman.

name: Riding in Cars with Boys
title: 2001 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 2h 12m
description: Beverly Donofrio, a fifteen-year-old teenager, is forced to sacrifice her aspirations to become a writer when she becomes pregnant and is asked to marry Ray, the father of her child.

name: Pay It Forward
title: 2000 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 2h 3m
description: Inspired by a school assignment, young Trevor comes up with an idea that changes many lives. He decides that instead of returning a favour, he will pay it forward by doing good deeds for three people.

name: Where the Heart Is
title: 2000 ‧ Romance/Comedy ‧ 2 hours
description: Abandoned by her boyfriend, Novalee, a 17-year-old pregnant girl, takes shelter in a supermarket. However, when she delivers her baby and becomes a national sensation, she tries to rebuild her life.

name: The Book of Eli
title: 2010 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 58m
description: In a post-apocalyptic state, Eli comes across a ramshackle town on his journey westward. There, he meets Carnegie, a power-hungry man searching for a sacred book that Eli is tasked to protect.

name: Deliver Us from Eva
title: 2003 ‧ Romance/Comedy ‧ 1h 46m
description: Tired of their partners' meddling and domineering sister Eva, three men hire a playboy to date her. However, when the two fall in love, the men scramble to separate them.

name: The Mighty
title: 1998 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 1h 40m
description: Two young boys are social outcasts in their community due to their disabilities and broken home lives. When they are paired together, they form a bond over their shared circumstances.

name: Something the Lord Made
title: 2004 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 hours
description: Cardiac pioneers Alfred Blalock and Vivien Thomas, who developed the procedure to treat blue baby syndrome, share a complicated and unstable relationship.

name: The Cider House Rules
title: 1999 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 2h 6m
description: During World War II, an orphan grows up under the tutelage of a doctor who runs an orphanage. However, he yearns for freedom and soon decides to leave in order to make a life for himself.

name: Remember the Titans
title: 2000 ‧ Sport/Drama ‧ 1h 53m
description: Herman Boone, an African-American, is appointed as the new coach of a high school team. The team is playing as a racially-integrated team for the first time.

name: Prison Song
title: 2001 ‧ Musical/Drama ‧ 1h 34m
description: Life has dealt Elijah (Q-Tip) a tough hand. His stepfather is sent to prison, and his mother (Mary J. Blige) becomes institutionalized. Elijah spends time in foster homes, but his talent for photography leads to a college scholarship offer. Soon, however, events spiral out of hand, and Elijah finds himself behind bars for accidentally killing a man (Fat Joe) during a fight. Assisted by his understanding lawyer (Elvis Costello), Elijah fights for his dignity and for prison reform.

name: The Great Debaters
title: 2007 ‧ Drama/Historical drama ‧ 2h 6m
description: Melvin B Tolson, a professor at Wiley College, motivates his students to form the first-ever debate team. Hard work pays off when the team defeats Harvard in the national championship.

name: Men of Honor
title: 2000 ‧ Action/Drama ‧ 2h 9m
description: Inspired by the bravery of a diver, a US Navy recruit resolves to overcome his educational shortcomings and racism in order to become the force's first black master diver, even after losing a leg.

name: Blue Hill Avenue
title: 2001 ‧ Drama ‧ 2 hours
description: Four friends enter the drug trade in Boston in the late 1970s: Tristan (Allen Payne), Money (Aaron D. Spears), E-Bone and Simon. With the consent of a South End crime boss, Benny (Clarence Williams III), they quickly rise in the drug game, while the leader of the group, Tristan, keeps his double life a secret from his clueless parents. However, as the 1970s pass to the 2000s, a police investigation threatens to ignite a violent feud among the tight-knit friends.

name: John Q.
title: 2002 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 1h 56m
description: John Q Archibald lives with his wife, Denise, and young son Michael. But when Michael needs an emergency heart transplant that John can't afford, he vows to do anything to keep his son alive.

name: Man on Fire
title: 2004 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 2h 26m
description: John, an assassin in Mexico, is hired as a bodyguard, a job he does not want to accept. However, he agrees and promises to take revenge on the kidnapper of the child from the family he is protecting.

name: Three Days In The Life Of Lt. Kravtsov
title: 2012 film
description: Nikolai Kravtsov, a young lieutenant, realises that death is inevitable when he is sent as a platoon commander in the Great Patriotic War. However, he is determined to survive.

name: The White Tiger
title: 2021 ‧ Crime ‧ 2h 5m
description: A rich Indian family's ambitious driver uses his wit and cunning to escape from poverty and rise to the top as an entrepreneur.

name: Road to Berlin
title: 2015 ‧ War/Action ‧ 1h 25m
description: All the soldiers from different regions in Russia fall into complex relationships and get into trouble. They all unite during the Second World War with a common purpose in mind.

name: Kalashnikov
title: 2020 ‧ War/Action ‧ 1h 50m
description: Kalashnikov, a tank driver and an inventor, gets wounded during WWII and realises that the latest Soviet machine gun is not up to the mark. So, he ends up inventing the AK-47 assault rifle.

name: Battalion
title: 2015 ‧ War/Action ‧ 2h 4m
description: Following the anti-monarchical February Revolution in Russia in 1917, the royalist Russian troops in WWI are disheartened. Their commanders set up an all-female battalion to fight the Central Powers.

name: Battle For Honor
title: 2010 ‧ War/Action ‧ 2h 18m
description: A war drama set during the Nazi invasion of the Soviet Union in June 1941, in which Russian troops held on to a border stronghold for nine days.

name: Soldier Boy
title: 2019 ‧ War/Action ‧ 1h 26m
description: Six-year-old Seryozha Aleshkov loses every member of his family to the war. Afterwards, a little game to preserve his innocence leads to a heroic outcome.

name: V2. Escape from Hell
title: 2021 ‧ War/Action ‧ 1h 58m
description: V2. Escape from Hell is a 2021 Russian prison action thriller war biopic film directed by Timur Bekmambetov. The film stars Thure Riefenstein, Pavel Priluchny, Pavel Chinarev and Daria Zlatopolskaya.

name: White Tiger
title: 2012 ‧ War/Action ‧ 1h 44m
description: During WWII, Naydenov, a wounded tank driver, suffers from amnesia. He believes a disappearing ghostly tank, White Tiger, had destroyed his tank and becomes obsessed with destroying the machine.

name: Tremors 4: The Legend Begins
title: 2004 ‧ Horror/Western ‧ 1h 41m
description: Unexplained deaths in the silver mine cause an uproar in the town of Rejection, Nevada. With mysterious creatures fostering in the valley, the mine's owner reaches the town to unveil the mystery.

name: Resident Evil: Apocalypse
title: 2004 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 34m
description: Alice wakes up to find that Raccoon city is infested with zombies and monsters. Later, she tries her best to find a way out of the city before it is too late.

name: Transformers One
title: 2024 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 44m
description: Once upon a time, Optimus Prime and Megatron were friends bonded like brothers who managed to change the fate of the Cybertron planet forever. This is their untold original story, before they end up being bitter opponents.

name: Starship Troopers
title: 1997 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 2h 15m
description: Johnny Rico completes his graduation and joins the Mobile Infantry to serve the nation. Soon, he finds himself fighting against alien bugs that are hell-bent on destroying life on Earth.

name: La Haine
title: 1995 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 1h 38m
description: After a youth is tortured by the police, a riot explodes on the streets of Paris. Vinz, Said and Hubert find a gun lost by the police in the riots and threaten to kill a cop if their friend dies.

name: Chungking Express
title: 1994 ‧ Romance/Crime ‧ 1h 42m
description: Two policemen based in Hong Kong go through struggles when one falls in love with a mysterious woman and the other falls for a server at a restaurant he visits often.

name: As I Was Moving Ahead Occasionally I Saw Brief Glimpses of Beauty
title: 2000 ‧ Documentary/Experimental ‧ 4h 48m
description: Avant-garde filmmaker Jonas Mekas reveals home movies of family and friends.

name: Happy as Lazzaro
title: 2018 ‧ Documentary/Drama ‧ 2h 5m
description: A naive young man, Lazzaro, is content with his life as a labourer on a farm. But an unlikely friendship with the marchioness's son changes Lazzaro's world.

name: Goodbye, Dragon Inn
title: 2003 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 1h 22m
description: In Taipei, a movie theater is closing, but not before one final film is shown -- "Dragon Inn," a 1967 actioner and the source of nostalgia for the moviegoers and employees in the old, decrepit and possibly haunted building. The workers include eccentric projectionist Hsiao-Kang (Lee Kang-sheng) and a crippled cashier (Shiang-chyi Chen). The patrons include a Japanese tourist (Kiyonobu Mitamura) and two ghostly actors from the original film who have come to mourn the passing of an era.

name: Tropical Malady
title: 2004 ‧ Romance/Fantasy ‧ 2 hours
description: Keng (Banlop Lomnoi) is a soldier stationed in a quiet Thai village where the days progress with methodical slowness. Not much happens of interest until Keng encounters local boy Tong (Sakda Kaewbuadee), and the pair begin a tentative romance. Then, in a surreal move typical of director Apichatpong Weerasethakul, the film splinters into a story about a soldier (also Lomnoi) searching for a lost boy in the jungle and meeting a vexing spirit (also Kaewbuadee).

name: Happy Together
title: 1997 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 1h 36m
description: Yiu and Po visit Argentina to mend their problematic relationship. As things turn worse, they part ways and start a new life. However, after Po reappears in Yiu's disillusioned life, chaos ensues.

name: Millennium Mambo
title: 2001 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 1h 59m
description: Yiu and Po visit Argentina to mend their problematic relationship. As things turn worse, they part ways and start a new life. However, after Po reappears in Yiu's disillusioned life, chaos ensues.

name: The Gleaners and I
title: 2000 ‧ Documentary ‧ 1h 22m
description: An 1867 painting by Jean-Francois Millet inspired septuagenarian documentarian Agnes Varda to cross the French countryside to videotape people who scavenge. Taking everything from surplus in the fields, to rubbish in trashcans, to oysters washed up after a storm, the "gleaners" range from those sadly in need to those hoping to recreate the community activity of centuries past, and still others who use whatever they find to cobble together a rough art. Highlighted by Varda's amusing narration.

name: Werckmeister Harmonies
title: 2000 ‧ Mystery/Drama ‧ 2h 25m
description: A mysterious circus excites a small Hungarian town into a rebellion when a promised act doesn't perform.

name: Ratcatcher
title: 1999 ‧ Drama/Coming-of-age story ‧ 1h 34m
description: James Gillespie (William Eadie) is 12 years old. The world he knew is changing. Haunted by a secret, he has become a stranger in his own family. He is drawn to the canal where he creates a world of his own. He finds an awkward tenderness with Margaret Anne (Leanne Mullen), a vulnerable 14 year old expressing a need for love in all the wrong ways, and befriends Kenny (John Miller), who possesses an unusual innocence in spite of the harsh surroundings.

name: Amélie
title: 2001 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 2h 2m
description: Despite being caught in her imaginative world, Amelie, a young waitress, decides to help people find happiness. Her quest to spread joy leads her on a journey where she finds true love.

name: Mystery Train
title: 1989 ‧ Comedy/Crime ‧ 1h 53m
description: The lives of a few individuals collide when they all check into a sleazy Memphis hotel, including a couple, a gang of robbers, a night clerk and the spirit of Elvis.

name: The Ballad of Buster Scruggs
title: 2018 ‧ Western/Comedy ‧ 2h 12m
description: An anthology containing six short films all occurring in 19th-century post-Civil War America during the settling of the Old West.

name: Night on Earth
title: 1991 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 2h 9m
description: Five different people in five cities board cabs in the night and have interesting and overwhelming conversations about life, religion and culture with their taxi drivers.

name: Dead Man Walking
title: 1995 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 2h 2m
description: Honouring the request of a desperate man, Sister Helen Prejean writes to the condemned killer of two teenage lovers. However, she is unprepared for the relationship that develops as a result.

name: Coffee and Cigarettes
title: 2003 ‧ Comedy/Indie film ‧ 1h 36m
description: An anthology of eleven vignettes, where actors and characters talk to each other about the most mundane topics over a cup of coffee and cigarettes.

name: Dinner Rush
title: 2000 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 1h 39m
description: Louis Cropa, a part-time bookmaker, decides to turn his family-owned restaurant into one of the most famous places to visit in TriBeCa, NYC, with the help of his son.

name: Wag the Dog
title: 1997 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 1h 37m
description: The president of the US is caught in a sex scandal a few days before the elections. To avoid media outburst and public outrage, Conrad Bean, his aide, constructs a fake war against Albania.

name: Patriot Games
title: 1992 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 57m
description: An ex-CIA agent stops a terrorist kidnapping attempt of a minister in London and ends up slaying one of the kidnappers. But the dead man's brother vows revenge against the agent and his family.

name: A Brighter Summer Day
title: 1991 ‧ Crime/Romance ‧ 3h 57m
description: When 14-year-old Si'r falls in love with Ming, the leader of a youth gang in the locality, he starts getting increasingly involved with the gang, gradually drawing him into a world of violence.

name: Sonatine
title: 1993 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 1h 34m
description: Several yakuza from Tokyo are sent to Okinawa to help end a gang war. The war escalates and the Tokyo drifters decide to lay low at the beach.

name: Hana-bi
title: 1997 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 1h 43m
description: Yoshitaka Nishi leaves the police force and borrows money from the mob to spend time with his dying wife. But he is forced to give up his ideals once again to pay back the criminals.

name: Fallen Angels
title: 1995 ‧ Crime/Romance ‧ 1h 39m
description: An assassin goes through obstacles as he attempts to escape his violent lifestyle despite the opposition of his partner, who is secretly attracted to him.

name: Full Metal Yakuza
title: 1997 ‧ Action/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 44m
description: Full Metal Yakuza is a 1997 Japanese tokusatsu action film directed by Takashi Miike. It was written by Itaru Era and based on a story by Hiroki Yamaguchi. Originally released in Japan's direct-to-video market, the film has gained more popularity because of the reputation of its controversial director.

name: The Bird People in China
title: 1998 ‧ Adventure/Fantasy ‧ 1h 58m
description: The Bird People in China is a 1998 Japanese comedy-drama film directed by Takashi Miike from a screenplay by his frequent collaborator Masa Nakamura. The film is considerably more mellow in tone compared to some of the director's more famous works.

name: Dead or Alive
title: 1999 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 45m
description: Ryuichi plans to become the kingpin of the Japanese underworld and is helped by his men. However, he encounters detective Jojima who is on a quest to end the mafia menace.

name: Hundreds of Beavers
title: 2022 ‧ Comedy/Action ‧ 1h 48m
description: A drunken applejack salesman must go from zero to hero and become North America's greatest fur trapper by defeating hundreds of beavers.

name: Ghost Dog: The Way of the Samurai
title: 1999 ‧ Crime/Thriller ‧ 1h 56m
description: A principled hitman finds himself under the radar of a local mobster while working for the American mafia. However, his ideals compel him to rebel against the mafia's code of ethics.

name: Sin City - Recut, Extended, Unrated
title: 2005 ‧ Crime/Action ‧ 2h 4m
description: Four individuals cross paths when they try to solve their personal problems and fight violence and corruption in the wretched town of Basin City, Washington.

name: Kill Bill: The Whole Bloody Affair
title: 2011 ‧ Action/Thriller
description: An assassin is shot and almost killed by her ruthless employer, Bill, and other members of their assassination circle – but she lives to plot her vengeance. Kill Bill: The Whole Bloody Affair is a complete edit of the two-part martial arts action films Kill Bill: Vol. 1 and Kill Bill: Vol. 2. The film was originally scheduled to be released as one part. However, due to the film's over 4 hour running time, it was split into two parts.

name: 101 Dalmatians II: Patch's London Adventure
title: 2002 ‧ Adventure/Comedy ‧ 1h 14m
description: Patch does not feel unique due to being one of 101 puppies. However, one day he gets a chance to meets Thunderbolt, a television hero, who enlists him on a publicity campaign.

name: Aladdin
title: 2019 ‧ Family/Musical ‧ 2h 8m
description: Aladdin, a kind thief, woos Jasmine, the princess of Agrabah, with the help of Genie. When Jafar, the grand vizier, tries to usurp the king, Jasmine, Aladdin and Genie must stop him from succeeding.

name: Cinderella
title: 2015 ‧ Family/Fantasy ‧ 1h 45m
description: Ella resides with her abusive stepmother and her daughters who continuously make her suffer at home. Her life changes when she meets a handsome man of nobility who gives her a chance to become free.

name: Beauty and the Beast
title: 2017 ‧ Family/Fantasy ‧ 2h 19m
description: A village girl embarks on a journey to save her father from a creature that has locked him in his dungeon. Eventually, she learns that the creature is a prince who has been cursed.

name: One Hundred and One Dalmatians
title: 1961 ‧ Family/Adventure ‧ 1h 19m
description: Evil heiress Cruella de Vil decides to make a fur coat for herself out of the skins of Dalmatian puppies. When she steals a litter of 15 puppies, it is up to their parents to rescue the innocent pups.

name: Maleficent
title: 2014 ‧ Family/Fantasy ‧ 1h 37m
description: Maleficent, a kind-hearted fairy who changed after her lover Stefan deceived her, places a curse on his daughter Aurora. But soon she realizes that only Aurora can bring peace to the troubled country.

name: Maleficent: Mistress of Evil
title: 2019 ‧ Family/Adventure ‧ 1h 58m
description: Maleficent alienates herself from Aurora when she opposes her engagement with Prince Phillip. Unknown to them, an enemy lurks, waiting to capitalise on their discord and destroy all that they love.

name: 101 Dalmatians
title: 1996 ‧ Adventure/Crime ‧ 1h 43m
description: Anita, a fashion designer, and Roger, a computer game writer, have to rescue the puppies of their dalmatians from Cruella De Vil, an insane woman, who wants to use their fur to make a coat.

name: Serendipity
title: 2001 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 31m
description: Jon and Sara decide to separate after a night of romance when they were shopping for their respective spouses. But destiny has other plans as it brings them together before their respective marriages.

name: The Notebook
title: 2004 ‧ Romance/Comedy ‧ 2h 1m
description: Noah, a poor man, falls in love with Allie who comes from wealth. They are forced to keep passion for each other aside due to societal pressure and a difference in the social stature of their families

name: Legally Blonde
title: 2001 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 36m
description: When Elle, a sorority queen, is dumped by her boyfriend as he plans to go to law school, she enrols in the same school to win him back. However, she discovers that there is more to her than her looks.

name: Notting Hill
title: 1999 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 2h 4m
description: A set of circumstances makes Anna Scott, a famous actress, fall in love with William Thacker, owner of a bookstore in Notting Hill. But the paparazzi's fascination with her complicates their bond.

name: Just like Heaven
title: 2005 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 48m
description: David, a lonely architect, finds an amazing apartment, only to discover it's haunted by the spirit of the previous tenant Elizabeth, an overachieving doctor. Eventually, he falls in love with her.

name: 50 First Dates
title: 2004 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 39m
description: Henry, against the idea of a committed romance with women, meets Lucy and is smitten with her. She too likes him. But unhappiness visits him when he realises she suffers from short-term memory loss.

name: The Wedding Planner
title: 2001 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 44m
description: When Mary Fiore, a wedding planner, is rescued by the handsome Steve Edison, she believes that she has found her true love. Things get out of control when she learns he is her client's fiance.

name: She's the Man
title: 2006 ‧ Comedy/Sport ‧ 1h 45m
description: When Viola's football team is dissolved and she is not allowed to play on the boys' team either, she disguises herself as her twin brother and participates in the tournament.

name: Erin Brockovich
title: 2000 ‧ Drama/Legal drama ‧ 2h 11m
description: When a single mother without employment becomes a legal assistant, she is determined to punish a powerful Californian energy corporation which has allegedly polluted a city's water supply network.

name: 10 Things I Hate About You
title: 1999 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 37m
description: As soon as Cameron, a newbie at Padua High School, finds Bianca, he falls in love with her. However, to date Bianca, he must first get her older sister Kate, a mean feminist, to date someone.

name: Bring It On
title: 2000 ‧ Comedy/Sport ‧ 1h 38m
description: Torrance, skipper of her San Diego-based high school's cheerleading squad, is shocked when she realises that her team's ex-captain plagiarised their best routines from another team.

name: Legally Blonde: The Musical
title: 2007 ‧ Musical/Comedy ‧ 3h 5m
description: Legally Blonde follows the story of sorority president Elle Woods as she crosses the country on a mission to find love at Harvard Law School. After discovering how the law can be used to help others, she uses her new found skills to defend a workout-queen in a murder trial, defying the odds and proving that pink can save the day!

name: Sweet Home Alabama
title: 2002 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 49m
description: Melanie, a New York-based fashion designer who is engaged to the city's most desirable bachelor, returns to Alabama to end her quarrelsome marriage with Jake. But he stubbornly refuses to divorce her.

name: Legally Blonde 2: Red, White & Blonde
title: 2003 ‧ Rom-com/Teen ‧ 1h 35m
description: Upon graduating, Elle Woods travels to Washington D.C. with the intention of persuading the politicians to ban animal testing, but the task is easier said than done.

name: The Intern
title: 2015 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 2h 1m
description: A seventy-year-old Ben Whittaker realises that retirement isn't an enjoyable experience. As a result, he decides to work as an intern at an online fashion store managed by an extremely sceptical boss.

name: Charlie's Angels
title: 2000 ‧ Action/Comedy ‧ 1h 38m
description: Natalie, Dylan and Alex are three beautiful and uniquely talented tough girls are given the task of finding the kidnapped owner of Knox Enterprises, Eric Knox, by their millionaire boss, Charlie.

name: Cruella
title: 2021 ‧ Comedy/Crime ‧ 2h 14m
description: Estella is a young and clever grifter who's determined to make a name for herself in the fashion world. She soon meets a pair of thieves who appreciate her appetite for mischief, and together they build a life for themselves on the streets of London. However, when Estella befriends fashion legend Baroness von Hellman, she embraces her wicked side to become the raucous and revenge-bent Cruella.

name: Now You See Me
title: 2013 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 1h 55m
description: The Horsemen, a group of four street magicians, are chased by FBI agent Dylan Rhodes and Interpol agent Alma Dray after they rob a huge sum of money that belongs to insurance magnate Arthur Tressler.

name: Miss Congeniality 2: Armed and Fabulous
title: 2005 ‧ Comedy/Mystery ‧ 1h 55m
description: After Miss USA and her companion get kidnapped, FBI agent Gracie goes undercover to Las Vegas for investigating the case. She decides to find them on her own even if it means disobeying direct orders.

name: Miss Congeniality
title: 2000 ‧ Comedy/Action ‧ 1h 49m
description: Gracie Hart, a tomboyish detective, is made to infiltrate the Miss United States beauty pageant as a contestant after her department learns that the event is under threat from an anonymous bomber.

name: Confessions of a Shopaholic
title: 2009 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 45m
description: Rebecca, a compulsive shopper, works as an advice columnist for a financial magazine, preaching what she hasn't practised. As her dream nears fulfilment, her shopaholic past threatens to haunt her.

name: Letters to Juliet
title: 2010 ‧ Romance/Comedy ‧ 1h 45m
description: While in Verona, Sophie joins a volunteer group who respond to letters seeking romantic advice. When she replies to a letter from Claire dated 1957, it inspires her to search for her long-lost love.

name: Leap Year
title: 2010 ‧ Drama/Melodrama ‧ 1h 40m
description: Anna Brady decides to travel to Dublin, Ireland, to propose to her boyfriend Jeremy on 29 February, a leap day. However, she faces several hindrances during the journey.

name: How to Lose a Guy in 10 Days
title: 2003 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 56m
description: Andie, a magazine writer, meets her date Benjamin, a marketing executive, after she decides to write a special column while he makes a bet. Unaware of their real intentions, they fall in love.

name: Monte Carlo
title: 2011 ‧ Comedy/Family ‧ 1h 49m
description: Grace, who is vacationing in Paris with her best friend and stepsister, is mistaken for a British heiress. The three women are whisked away to Monte Carlo, where they discover royalty and romance.

name: Wild Child
title: 2008 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 38m
description: A rebellious Malibu princess is sent off to a strict English boarding school by her father. Unwilling to accept the strict regime, she decides to misbehave, in the hope of being dismissed from school.

name: Rec 2
title: 2009 ‧ Horror/Action ‧ 1h 25m
description: Dr. Owen enters a forbidden building with his team to collect the blood sample of a girl to produce an antidote. But they encounter some evil creatures that attack them.

name: V/H/S/Beyond
title: 2024 ‧ Horror/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 54m
description: Six bloodcurdling tapes unleash horror in a sci-fi-inspired hellscape, pushing the boundaries of fear and suspense.

name: The Descent Part 2
title: 2009 ‧ Horror/Adventure ‧ 1h 34m
description: The authorities find a blood-covered Sarah Carter with no memory of what happened during the spelunking exploration. They decide to take her back to the caves where the incident occurred.

name: Rec
title: 2007 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 18m
description: A television reporter and her cameraman record the horrifying outbreak of a disease that turns humans into vicious cannibals.

name: A Painted House
title: 2003 ‧ Family/Drama ‧ 2 hours
description: This coming-of-age story set in 1952 Arkansas focuses on ten-year-old Luke Chandler, who lives with his parents and grandparents on a cotton farm. In a catastrophic sequence of events brought on by the harsh conditions in which he lives, Luke witnesses murder, love, childbirth, a devastating flood and the break-up of two families.

name: Faith's Song
title: 2017 ‧ Drama/Music ‧ 1h 43m
description: A girl's faith is tested after her parents are killed in a car crash and she is forced to move in with relatives who are non-believers. She wants to worship God through her singing, but faces ridicule and challenges to her piety at home and school.

name: A Question of Faith
title: 2017 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 44m
description: When three families find themselves in the middle of a crisis, they begin to question their beliefs. However, a series of events bring them together.

name: The Forge
title: 2024 ‧ Drama ‧ 2h 5m
description: A year out of high school with no plans for his future, a boy is challenged by his single mom and a successful businessman to start charting a better course for his life. Through the prayers of his mother and biblical discipleship from his new mentor, he begins discovering God's purpose for his life is so much more than he could hope for or imagine.

name: Like Arrows: The Art of Parenting
title: 2018 ‧ Drama
description: Charlie and Alice try to change their parenting strategy when conflict, rebellion and resentment overwhelm their family. To their surprise, they soon find that effective, lifelong solutions were closer than they had ever imagined.

name: The Perfect Host
title: 2010 ‧ Thriller/Comedy ‧ 1h 33m
description: John, a criminal, makes his way to a dinner party hosted by Warwick Wilson in order to find a place to hide after committing a bank robbery.

name: Her Boyfriend's Secret
title: 2018 ‧ Thriller/Drama ‧ 1h 25m
description: Melissa believes she has found the man of her dreams in John, a client of her business. However, a chance meeting with John's ex-girlfriend leads her to believe that he is hiding a dark secret.

name: Two Against Time
title: 2002 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 40m
description: When a single mother and her teenage daughter are both diagnosed with cancer, the discovery forces both mother and daughter to reassess their relationship and helps both sufferers to overcome the long-time antagonistic relationship that has developed between them.

name: Hostile Advances
title: 1996 ‧ Thriller/Drama
description: The true story about a young IRS agent who is stalked by a colleague. Her complaint of harassment is dismissed by the courts, but her campaign for justice leads eventually to a change in American law.

name: Fatal Honeymoon
title: 2012 ‧ Action/Thriller ‧ 1h 30m
description: Tina Watson drowns in an unfortunate accident while scuba diving with her husband Gabe on their honeymoon. Gabe is accused of murder and an investigation ensues to discover the truth behind her death.

name: Murder on Pleasant Drive
title: 2006 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 1h 30m
description: When Fran Smith goes missing without a trace, her daughter and sister dig deeper to learn of her whereabouts. Her husband John is a worthy suspect but her body is nowhere to be found.

name: The Blind
title: 2023 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 48m
description: In 1960s Louisiana, future "Duck Dynasty" star Phil Robertson falls in love and starts a family, but his demons soon threaten to tear everyone apart. As he seeks to conquer the shame of his past, he ultimately finds redemption in an unlikely place.

name: Love's Everlasting Courage
title: 2011 ‧ Western/Romance ‧ 1h 28m
description: After Clark's hardworking wife dies an untimely death due to fever, he, along with his young daughter Missie, decides to turn to his parents for care and support.

name: Love Begins
title: 2011 ‧ Romance/Western ‧ 1h 28m
description: Clark, a cowboy with dreams of travelling the world, falls in love with Ellen while working at a farm. Soon he becomes conflicted about staying back with Ellen or continuing with his journey.

name: New Life
title: 2016 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 1h 28m
description: Childhood sweethearts, Ben and Ava, who have known each other since they were seven, come to terms with a tragedy that changes their lives forever.

name: Hoovey
title: 2015 ‧ Sport/Drama ‧ 1h 31m
description: While practising, when Eric 'Hoovey' Elliot collapses on the floor, he learns that he has a tumour in his brain. After a dangerous and risky surgery, he begins to relearn everything.

name: A Lobster Tale
title: 2006 ‧ Family/Drama ‧ 1h 35m
description: Fisherman Cody is facing hardships on the work front and at home. While his wife feels neglected, his son gets bullied at school. It all changes when he finds a strange green moss with magical powers.

name: The Short History Of The Long Road
title: 2019 ‧ Adventure/Drama ‧ 1h 37m
description: A teenager has to confront the reality of life on the road after tragedy strikes.

name: Driveways
title: 2019 ‧ Drama/Comedy ‧ 1h 25m
description: A young boy and his mother head over to a late relative's home to clean out her belongings. There, the child forms a special bond with an old man who lives next door.

name: Mountain Top
title: 2017 ‧ Mystery/Drama ‧ 1h 42m
description: A lawyer-turned-preacher must embrace his former profession as he chooses to represent an eccentric man in a court to solve a case that is linked to his sober life in a small town.

name: The Untold Story 2
title: 1998 ‧ Horror/Crime ‧ 1h 31m
description: Chung and Kuen, a couple in a loveless marriage, welcome the latter's relative into their home. However, strange things begin to occur in their household when she arrives.

name: The Way Back Home
title: 2006 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 33m
description: New York attorney Spencer Krane pays a visit to his grandmother, after she suffers from a heart attack. But what starts as a simple visit becomes more about learning the importance of faith.

name: Wish Man
title: 2019 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 47m
description: Arizona motorcycle cop Frank Shankwitz meets a terminally ill boy named Michael and is inspired to change his life, leading to the creation of the Make-A-Wish foundation.

name: A Killer in the Family
title: 1983 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 1h 30m
description: Three brothers help their father escape from jail, but their love is betrayed when he leads them on a murder spree.

name: Blur Circle
title: 2016 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 32m
description: A single mother (Cora Vander Broek), still grieving the loss of her young son who disappeared two years earlier, meets a man (Matthew Brumlow) with a shrouded past while following up on a lead.

name: Arthur Hailey's Detective
title: 2005 ‧ Mystery/Thriller ‧ 2h 51m
description: Malcolm Ainslie, a priest-turned-detective, agrees to meet a serial killer before he is convicted to find out the reason behind the crimes he committed.

name: Accidental Texan
title: 2023 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 1h 44m
description: Stranded in Buffalo Gap, Texas, fledgling actor Erwin meets Merle, a veteran oil driller who's about to lose everything he owns. In desperate straits, Merle asks him to pose as his landman to fool the police and a corrupt oil company owner.

name: The Meanest Man in Texas
title: 2017 ‧ Thriller/Drama ‧ 1h 45m
description: After being sentenced to death for murder, Clyde Thompson is miraculously granted parole. Soon, he finds redemption and love with Julia Perryman.

name: Mockingbird Don't Sing
title: 2001 ‧ Drama/Indie film ‧ 1h 38m
description: In 1970, 13-year-old Katie Standon (Tarra Steele) gains national media attention for having suffered through one of the most extreme cases of child abuse ever discovered. After being locked in a closet for 12 years, Katie is unable to speak or function properly in the outside world. With the attention Katie now receives, researchers and social workers from all over offer to help her -- but not all of them have entirely pure intentions, as some only seek to garner fame from her spotlight.

name: A Matter of Justice
title: 1993 ‧ Thriller/Drama
description: In this adaptation of a true story, young marine Chris Brown (Jason London) returns home to his parents, Mary (Patty Duke) and Jack (Martin Sheen), with his new wife, a manipulative older woman named Dusty (Alexandra Powers). Mary does not support the marriage and urges Chris to divorce Dusty, but Chris ignores her pleas and claims that they are in love. When Chris is found dead, Mary suspects Dusty of killing him, and vows to avenge his murder and gain custody of her granddaughter.

name: Trial by Fire
title: 1996 ‧ Thriller/Drama ‧ 1h 34m
description: Her husband and a lawyer (Keith Carradine) stand by a high-school teacher (Gail O'Grady) charged with sexual assault after a student's (Michael Bowen) suicide.

name: Bless You, Prison
title: 2002 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 30m
description: Nicole Valery-Grossu (Maria Ploae) is an intellectual political activist living in communist Romania. She is arrested for her anti-government views and sent to prison without a trial. She is then subjected to solitary confinement and rigorous interrogation. After months of abuse, Nicole has a religious awakening. Through her newfound faith, she finds the strength to endure the hardships imposed by her captors and inspires her fellow inmates by continuing her outspoken resistance.

name: Fight for Justice: The Nancy Conn Story
title: 1995 ‧ Thriller/Drama ‧ 1h 29m
description: When a woman is stalked by an escaped psychopath who had previously kidnapped and killed her cousin, she launches a dangerous crusade to put the man back behind bars.

name: The Unspoken Truth
title: 1995 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 45m
description: A woman tries to take the fall for another of her husband's violent outbreaks, which results in a man's death, but her actions may spell danger for her young daughter.

name: Shattered Innocence
title: 1988 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 33m
description: A Kansas cheerleader (Jonna Lee) turns 18, moves to Los Angeles and becomes a porno star hooked on cocaine.

name: Escape from Terror: The Teresa Stamper Story
title: 1995 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 30m
description: Teresa's blissful marriage crumbles after her husband starts battering her and consuming drugs. However, he continues to stalk her, shoots her boyfriend and abducts her and their daughter.

name: The Execution of Wanda Jean
title: 2002 ‧ Documentary/Crime ‧ 1h 28m
description: "The Execution of Wanda Jean" chronicles the life-and-death battle of Wanda Jean Allen. By telling one woman's story, the film becomes an unforgettable exploration into one of America's most controversial moral and political dilemmas: the death penalty. "The Execution of Wanda Jean" is an unflinching investigation of the role that poverty, mental health, race, and sexuality play within the criminal justice system.

name: Lies in Plain Sight
title: 2010 ‧ Mystery/Drama ‧ 1h 30m
description: Sofia, a sightless girl, is guided through her adolescence by her cousin Eva. When Eva commits suicide, a shocked Sofia starts investigating and uncovers unpleasant secrets related to their childhood.

name: The Cheating Pact
title: 2013 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 1h 25m
description: Three high school teenagers coerce Meredith, a shy but smart student, to take the College Entrance Test on their behalf. When Meredith winds up dead, all the three girls become the prime suspects.

name: Sworn to Vengeance
title: 1993 ‧ Thriller/Mystery ‧ 1h 37m
description: Sergeant Stewart sets off to investigate the murder of three innocent kids with the help of a woman, the only witness in the case.

name: A Murder of Crows
title: 1998 ‧ Thriller/Action ‧ 1h 42m
description: A disbarred lawyer forgoes the writing of his own book and takes credit for a late friend's book. The book is a murder mystery and becomes a huge success.

name: Outrage!
title: 1986 ‧ Thriller/Drama ‧ 2 hours
description: Dennis Riordan (Robert Preston) is enraged after the man who raped and murdered his daughter is relieved of punishment because of a legal loophole. Riordan then assumes the role of judge and jury and kills the man himself. He subsequently refuses to plea insanity, leaving his defense attorney, Brad Gordon (Beau Bridges), in a tough spot. Gordon then resorts to desperate measures and calls the judge who released Riordan's victim to the stand for a tense debate of legal ethics.

name: Murder in Texas
title: 1981 ‧ Drama ‧ 3h 20m
description: John Hill (Sam Elliott) is a plastic surgeon who may not be what he seems. His first wife, Joan Robinson (Farrah Fawcett), is a socialite who falls ill and dies under suspicious circumstances. Hill proceeds to marry his mistress, divorcée Ann Kurth (Katharine Ross), with whom he conducted an affair while still married to Joan. Ash Robinson (Andy Griffith), Joan's father, is convinced that Hill murdered his daughter. And he is intent on bringing the doctor to justice.

name: Texas Justice
title: 1995 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 2h 55m
description: Millionaire Cullen Davis marries the not-so-rich Priscilla. Their relationship turns sour and Cullen kills Priscilla's daughter and lover. He hires a famous attorney, but things do not go as planned.

name: The Girl Who Played with Fire
title: 2009 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 2h 9m
description: Computer hacker Lisbeth tries to investigate and bust a sex trafficking network jointly with the journalist Mikael. But when she is accused of killing three people, she is on the run from the police.

name: The Girl with the Dragon Tattoo
title: 2011 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 2h 38m
description: Mikael Blomkvist, a journalist, hires Lisbeth Salander, a computer hacker, to solve the mystery of a woman who has been missing for forty years. The two soon discover more than they bargained for.

name: Warlock
title: 1989 ‧ Horror/Fantasy ‧ 1h 43m
description: Horror tale of a 17th century warlock who is transported into contemporary Los Angeles. He tries to reunite portions of a Devil's Book that can destroy mankind, and a witch hunter is out to stop him.

name: Jacob's Ladder
title: 1990 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 53m
description: A postal worker is haunted by flashbacks from his earlier marriage, his torturous days of duty during the Vietnam War and his now-dead son.

name: Night of the Creeps
title: 1986 ‧ Horror/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 30m
description: An alien experiment containing slug-like organisms crashes Earth and infects a fraternity member. Mayhem ensues when a couple of college boys discover the cryogenically frozen corpse.

name: The Exorcist III
title: 1990 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 50m
description: Lieutenant Kinderman sets out to investigate a series of brutal murders with the trademark of a serial killer, The Gemini. However, he uncovers disturbing facts which leave him troubled.

name: Society
title: 1989 ‧ Horror/Mystery ‧ 1h 39m
description: A California teen's worst nightmares about his parents come true when he returns home to find a grotesque party in full swing.

name: Hellraiser
title: 1987 ‧ Horror/Fantasy ‧ 1h 52m
description: A couple moves to an old house to find the man's brother and the wife's former lover who has turned into an ugly beast. He now bids the woman to bring him human sacrifices to help him be whole again.

name: The People Under the Stairs
title: 1991 ‧ Horror/Comedy ‧ 1h 42m
description: Three burglars attempt to rob a house and get trapped inside. They are haunted by children who stay under the staircase of the house.

name: From Beyond
title: 1986 ‧ Horror/Sci-fi ‧ 1h 26m
description: Obsessive scientist Dr. Pretorius (Ted Sorel) successfully discovers a way to access a parallel universe of pleasure by tapping into the brain's pineal gland. When he is seemingly killed by forces from this other dimension, his assistant, Dr. Crawford Tillinghast (Jeffrey Combs), is accused of the murder. After psychiatrist Katherine McMichaels (Barbara Crampton) and detective Bubba Brownlee (Ken Foree) take the case, the trio risks a return to the other world in order to solve the mystery.

name: Night of the Demons
title: 1988 ‧ Horror/Comedy ‧ 1h 30m
description: A group of teens decides to have a Halloween party up at the deserted funeral parlor where they accidentally awaken some evil force and find themselves trapped, with no way out.

name: Prince of Darkness
title: 1987 ‧ Horror/Fantasy ‧ 1h 42m
description: While cleaning the basement in his church, Father Loomis comes across a canister filled with a volatile green substance. With help from Professor Birack, he realises that the liquid is Satan's spirit.

name: Near Dark
title: 1987 ‧ Horror/Western ‧ 1h 34m
description: Cowboy Caleb Colton (Adrian Pasdar) meets gorgeous Mae (Jenny Wright) at a bar, and the two have an immediate attraction. But when Mae turns out to be a vampire and bites Caleb on the neck, their relationship gets complicated. Wracked with a craving for human blood, Caleb is forced to leave his family and ride with Mae and her gang of vampires, including the evil Severen. Along the way Caleb must decide between his new love of Mae and the love of his family.

name: Pumpkinhead
title: 1988 ‧ Horror/Indie film ‧ 1h 26m
description: After a group of motorists kill his son, Ed Harley consults a witch to summon Pumpkinhead, a vicious creature, to hunt the murderers. He immediately regrets his decision when things take a dark turn.

name: Come and See
title: 1985 ‧ War/Horror ‧ 2h 26m
description: Florya joins the Soviet Army against his family's wishes. After being subjected to unfair treatment in the army, he returns home and finds his family massacred by the German forces.

name: Hacksaw Ridge
title: 2016 ‧ War/Drama ‧ 2h 19m
description: After Desmond Doss nearly kills his younger brother, he refuses to handle weapons or engage in war. However, post the Japanese attack on Pearl Harbour, he joins the American army as a combat medic.

name: They Shall Not Grow Old
title: 2018 ‧ Documentary/War ‧ 1h 39m
description: Using state-of-the-art technology and materials from the BBC and Imperial War Museum, filmmaker Peter Jackson allows the story of World War I to be told by the men who were there. Life on the front is explored through the voices of the soldiers, who discuss their feelings about the conflict, the food they ate, the friends they made and their dreams of the future.

name: Fury
title: 2014 ‧ War/Action ‧ 2h 14m
description: Wardaddy, along with his crew of five members, embarks on a mission that puts many lives in danger. The crew members realise that the odds are against them, but still decide to attack the Nazi army.

name: Dead Poets Society
title: 1989 ‧ Comedy/Drama ‧ 2h 8m
description: A group of students in a highly conservative boarding school learn to rebel against the status quo and find deeper meaning in life with the help of their new poetry teacher.

name: A Higher Law
title: 2021 ‧ Thriller ‧ 2h 3m
description: Ecaterina, high school religion teacher and wife of the town priest, gets involved with a 16-year-old student who has a troubled past. She tries to keep him under control, but loses her own sense of control in the process.

name: Dogs Don't Wear Pants
title: 2019 ‧ Comedy/Romance ‧ 1h 45m
description: The story follows Juha who develops an unexpected but powerful connection with a dominatrix named Mona, following a tragic event in his life that has left him emotionally paralysed. His dangerous addiction to suffocation is reciprocated by Mona leading them both down a wild and crazy path towards emotional enlightenment.

name: Quills
title: 2000 ‧ Drama ‧ 2h 4m
description: Marquis De Sade, a writer, caused political turmoil quite often with his writing. So, the state emperor takes away his ink and quills. Sade, then seeks the help of Madeline, a laundry girl.

name: The Piano
title: 1993 ‧ Romance/Drama ‧ 2h 1m
description: A mute woman and her daughter suffer exile in New Zealand and bring with them a piano. She is then set to marry a rich landlord but a peasant begins to fall in love with her.

name: Notes on a Scandal
title: 2006 ‧ Thriller/Crime ‧ 1h 38m
description: When a disgruntled veteran high school teacher realizes that her friend, a young and married art teacher, is having an affair with a fifteen year old student, she makes sexual advances of her own.

name: The Violin Player
title: 1994 ‧ Drama ‧ 1h 35m
description: The Violin Player is a 1994 French-Belgian drama film directed by Charles Van Damme. It was entered into the 1994 Cannes Film Festival.

name: Taste of Cherry
title: 1997 ‧ Drama/Comedy ‧ 1h 35m
description: A desperate middle-aged man, who wants to commit suicide, searches for an assistant who will bury him in the grave which he has already dug for himself.

name: Children of Heaven
title: 1997 ‧ Family/Sport ‧ 1h 29m
description: Siblings Ali and Zahra make an intricate arrangement to conceal the loss of Zahra's pair of shoes. However, when it becomes difficult to do so, Ali decides to participate in a race to win new shoes.

name: It's a Wonderful Life
title: 1946 ‧ Family/Fantasy ‧ 2h 10m
description: When a frustrated businessman, George Bailey, becomes suicidal, an angel from heaven, Clarence, is sent to him. To his change of heart, she shows him what life would have been without his existence.

name: The Monster
title: 1994 ‧ Comedy/Crime ‧ 1h 52m
description: Authorities use a policewoman to trap an innocent misfit who was mistaken for a notorious sex criminal and killer.

name: My Best Friend Anne Frank
title: 2021 ‧ War/Drama ‧ 1h 43m
description: Based on the real-life relationship between Anne Frank and Hannah Goslar, from Nazi-occupied Amsterdam to their harrowing reunion in a concentration camp.

name: A Beautiful Life
title: 2023 ‧ Romance/Musical ‧ 1h 39m
description: Elliott, a young fisherman with an extraordinary voice, gets the opportunity of a lifetime when he is discovered by the successful and well-known music manager Suzanne. Suzanne soon pairs Elliott with her divorced daughter and music producer, Lilly. On his way to stardom, the struggles of his past threaten not only his big break, but also his budding love for Lilly.

name: Train of Life (Zug des Lebens)
title: 1998 ‧ Comedy/War ‧ 1h 43m
description: The inhabitants of a small Jewish village in Central Europe organize a deportation train so that they can escape the atrocities of the Nazis and flee to Palestine.

name: Cinema Paradiso
title: 1988 ‧ Drama/Melodrama ‧ 2h 35m
description: Salvatore, a famous film director, returns to his hometown for the funeral of the local theatre's film projectionist, Alfredo. He reminisces about his life as a young boy falling in love with cinema.

name: A Bag of Marbles
title: 2017 ‧ War/Drama ‧ 1h 50m
description: Two Jewish brothers, aged 10 and 12, flee from Paris in the year 1941 to escape the Nazi invasion and reunite with their family.

name: The Boy in the Striped Pajamas
title: 2008 ‧ War/Thriller ‧ 1h 34m
